Creating a Map in Power Bi

Our 2nd visual will be a map

Steps:

1. Hover your mouse on the indicated visual then  click to select it

2. Use the icons on the edges to resize it 

Steps:

1. To populate the map, click on the Pre-Users Table to expand it

2. Click on the Latitude Column and drop it on the Latitude tab

3. Click on the Longitude Column and drop it on the Longitude tab


Adding calculated columns and measures on the map

Steps:

1. Click on the ADF_Marketing_PreUserActivity_Group table  to expand it

2. Click on the color column and drag it on the legend tab

3. Click on SessionCnt column and add it to the size tab, using the downward pointer, choose 'Count' function

4. Click on the SessionConversion % measure and add it to the  Tooltips tab


Hover your mouse on the map

The red dot shows the % of the PreUser who didn't register on the same day by location.

Hover your mouse on the map

The Blue dot shows the  % of the PreUser who  registered on the same day by location.
